HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1352
By Bulso
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Klaire Davis on her service to the
Franklin Special School District.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to offer
recognition to those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Klaire Davis is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished herself
as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Miss Davis has served and continues to serve as a mentor for new teachers
in the Franklin Special School District; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Department of Education has previously named Miss Davis
as a Reward Schools Ambassador, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive influence
she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Klaire Davis, a teacher at Moore Elementary School, was one of only fifteen
educators chosen for the Tennessee Reward Schools Ambassador Program, an initiative that
enlists highly effective teachers to share best practices and improve student achievement
throughout the State; and
WHEREAS, teachers of the Ambassador Program are selected from Reward Schools,
which are recognized as the State's top performing schools in academic achievement and
measurable progress; each Ambassador has earned an overall score of 5, the highest rating
possible on the State's teacher evaluations; and
WHEREAS, Miss Davis's service as a mentor for new teachers and her selection as a
Reward Schools Ambassador are a tremendous source of pride for her school and her
community; and
HJR1352
017763
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Klaire Davis truly epitomizes the dedicated teacher who is wholly committed
to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we congratulate Klaire Davis on her service to the Franklin Special School
District, commend her exceptional service to the children of Tennessee, and extend to her our
best wishes for continued success in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
